Adelaide Hawley Cumming https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adelaide_Hawley_Cumming 0 Adelaide Hawley Cumming (born Dieta Adelaide Fish; March 6, 1905 – December 21, 1998) was an American vaudeville performer, radio host, television star and living trademark for General Mills, and in later years, a teacher.
